docs.abstract: Last summer, China unveiled a plan to become the world’s leader in artificial intelligence, challenging the longtime role of the United States.
docs.snippet: Last summer, China unveiled a plan to become the world’s leader in artificial intelligence, challenging the longtime role of the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In July, China unveiled a plan to become the world leader in artificial intelligence and create an industry worth $150 billion to its economy by 2030.

headline.main: As China Marches Forward on A.I., the White House Is Silent

docs.abstract: Older tech companies have long had ties with military and intelligence. But employees at internet outfits like Google are wary of too much cooperation.
docs.snippet: Older tech companies have long had ties with military and intelligence. But employees at internet outfits like Google are wary of too much cooperation.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — There is little doubt that the Defense Department needs help from Silicon Valley’s biggest companies as it pursues work on artificial intelligence. The question is whether the people who work at those companies are willing to cooperate.

docs.abstract: A microprocessor once found mostly in machines used for computer games turns out to have a role in both artificial intelligence systems and the mining of digital currencies.
docs.snippet: A microprocessor once found mostly in machines used for computer games turns out to have a role in both artificial intelligence systems and the mining of digital currencies.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Two technology booms — some people might call them frenzies — are combining to turn a once-obscure type of microprocessor into a must-have but scarce commodity.

headline.main: Why A.I. and Cryptocurrency Are Making One Type of Computer Chip Scarce
headline.print_headline: A Computer Chip Shortage Is Linked to 2 Tech Booms: A.I. and Digital Currencies

docs.abstract: On Sunday, a woman in Arizona died after being struck by a self-driving car operated by Uber. Here is a guide to how autonomous vehicles operate.
docs.snippet: On Sunday, a woman in Arizona died after being struck by a self-driving car operated by Uber. Here is a guide to how autonomous vehicles operate.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Sunday night, a woman died after she was hit by a self-driving car operated by Uber in Tempe, Ariz. The car was operating autonomously, though a safety driver was behind the wheel, according to a statement from the local police.

headline.main: How Driverless Cars See the World Around Them
headline.print_headline: How Driverless Vehicles See the World

docs.abstract: “This is for building real long-term relationships, not just hookups,” Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, said in an apparent jab at dating apps like Tinder.
docs.snippet: “This is for building real long-term relationships, not just hookups,” Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, said in an apparent jab at dating apps like Tinder.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN JOSE, Calif. — Mark Zuckerberg may have laughed off questions that Facebook is too powerful when he appeared in front of Congress last month. But for the companies in the online dating business, there was nothing amusing about the news that the social network was about to bring its heft into their arena.

headline.main: For More Than Just Friends? Facebook Will Soon Offer a Dating Service

byline.original: By Cade Metz and Sheera Frenkel

docs.abstract: The U.S. and China are threatening a global trade war as they look to protect their most advanced industries.
docs.snippet: The U.S. and China are threatening a global trade war as they look to protect their most advanced industries.
docs.lead_paragraph: The United States undercut China’s technology ambitions on Tuesday, advancing a new rule that would limit the ability of Chinese telecommunications companies to sell their products in this country.

headline.main: Huawei and ZTE Hit Hard as U.S. Moves Against Chinese Tech Firms
headline.print_headline: U.S. Limiting Chinese Sales In Tech Battle

byline.original: By Raymond Zhong, Paul Mozur and Jack Nicas

docs.abstract: The Facebook chief executive has vowed to clean up the social network, but his company has failed to stop even those impersonating him from swindling people.
docs.snippet: The Facebook chief executive has vowed to clean up the social network, but his company has failed to stop even those impersonating him from swindling people.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — A Facebook notification on Gary Bernhardt’s phone woke him up one night last November with incredible news: a message from Mark Zuckerberg himself, saying that he had won $750,000 in the Facebook lottery.

headline.main: How Fake Mark Zuckerbergs Scam Facebook Users Out of Their Cash
headline.print_headline: Swindled on Facebook By Fake Marks and Sheryls

docs.abstract: Tax forms filed by OpenAI provide insight into the enormous salaries and bonuses paid to artificial intelligence specialists across the world.
docs.snippet: Tax forms filed by OpenAI provide insight into the enormous salaries and bonuses paid to artificial intelligence specialists across the world.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — One of the poorest-kept secrets in Silicon Valley has been the huge salaries and bonuses that experts in artificial intelligence can command. Now, a little-noticed tax filing by a research lab called OpenAI has made some of those eye-popping figures public.

headline.main: A.I. Researchers Are Making More Than $1 Million, Even at a Nonprofit

docs.abstract: Developers are working on or have completed a string of resort and hotel projects near the Catskill Mountains, signs of progress that hearten residents.
docs.snippet: Developers are working on or have completed a string of resort and hotel projects near the Catskill Mountains, signs of progress that hearten residents.
docs.lead_paragraph: THOMPSON, N.Y. — Patti Greco Sunshine, 57, a longtime resident of this town near the Catskill Mountains in Sullivan County, has watched as the region’s once-mighty hospitality industry literally crumbled around her.

headline.main: In the Catskills, New Hope for the Return of Tourism
headline.print_headline: A Second Act for the Borscht Belt

docs.abstract: The shift by the American president could ease tensions ahead of a visit to Washington by Liu He, a vice premier in the Beijing government.
docs.snippet: The shift by the American president could ease tensions ahead of a visit to Washington by Liu He, a vice premier in the Beijing government.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s recent threat to impose tariffs on as much as $150 billion worth of Chinese goods appeared to be the first volley in what looked like a full-scale trade war with the nation’s greatest economic adversary. Now, suddenly, Mr. Trump seems ready to make peace.

headline.main: Trump Shifts From Trade War Threats to Concessions in Rebuff to Hard-Liners
headline.print_headline: About-Face on Trade With China Stings White House Hard-Liners

byline.original: By Ana Swanson, Mark Landler and Keith Bradsher
